==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bonfire
<hw>Bon"fire`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>bonefire</ets>, <ets>banefire</ets>, orig. a fire of bones;
<ets>bone</ets> + <ets>fire</ets>; but cf. also Prov. E. <ets>bun</ets>
a dry stalk.]</ety> <def>A large fire built in the open air, as an
expression of public joy and exultation, or for amusement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Full soon by <qex>bonfire</qex> and by bell,⟦br⟧
We learnt our liege was passing well.</q> <rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bongo</ent>⟦br⟧
